rounded-2xl shadow-xl shadow-cyan-500/20\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-globe w-8 h-8 sm:w-10 sm:h-10 text-white\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"></circle><path d=\"M12 2a14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 20 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0-20\"></path><path d=\"M2 12h20\"></path></svg></div></div><h1 class=\"text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight\">Baby Names by Language — Multilingual Name Guide</h1><p class=\"text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed\">Explore beautiful baby names from different languages including Urdu, Arabic, Hindi, Sanskrit, Hebrew, and Greek. Discover 60,000+ multilingual names with detailed meanings and rich cultural significance from around the world.</p></div></div></section><section class=\"py-12 sm:py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-white/50\"><div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center\">Explore Names by Language</h2><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 sm:gap-8\"><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-purple-600 p-6 text-white\"><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-globe w-8 h-8\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"></circle><path d=\"M12 2a14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 20 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0-20\"></path><path d=\"M2 12h20\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-sm font-medium bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded-full\">15,000<!-- --> names</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2\">Urdu Baby Names</h3><p class=\"text-sm opacity-90 leading-relaxed\">Beautiful Urdu names with deep meanings and poetic elegance. Urdu names combine Persian, Arabic, and Turkic influences, creating names that flow melodically and carry profound significance.</p></div><div class=\"p-6\"><div class=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6\"><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Zainab</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Fragrant flower</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Ayaan</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Gift of God</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Iman</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Faith, belief</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-purple-100 text-purple-700\">unisex</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Zara</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Princess, flower</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div></div><a class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700\" href=\"/names/religion/islamic/1\">Explore all <!-- -->Urdu<!-- --> names<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-right w-4 h-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m9 18 6-6-6-6\"></path></svg></a></div></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-500 to-indigo-600 p-6 text-white\"><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-book-open w-8 h-8\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M12 7v14\"></path><path d=\"M3 18a1 1 0 0 1-1-1V4a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h5a4 4 0 0 1 4 4 4 4 0 0 1 4-4h5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v13a1 1 0 0 1-1 1h-6a3 3 0 0 0-3 3 3 3 0 0 0-3-3z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-sm font-medium bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded-full\">25,000<!-- --> names</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2\">Arabic Baby Names</h3><p class=\"text-sm opacity-90 leading-relaxed\">Classic Arabic names rooted in the Quran and Islamic tradition. These names honor the 99 names of Allah and reflect virtues like mercy, wisdom, and strength that are central to Islamic values.</p></div><div class=\"p-6\"><div class=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6\"><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Muhammad</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Praised, commendable</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Fatima</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Captivating, one who abstains</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Omar</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Long-lived, prosperous</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Layla</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Night, dark beauty</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div></div><a class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700\" href=\"/names/religion/islamic/1\">Explore all <!-- -->Arabic<!-- --> names<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-right w-4 h-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m9 18 6-6-6-6\"></path></svg></a></div></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-500 to-orange-600 p-6 text-white\"><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-sparkles w-8 h-8\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M11.017 2.814a1 1 0 0 1 1.966 0l1.051 5.558a2 2 0 0 0 1.594 1.594l5.558 1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0 1.966l-5.558 1.051a2 2 0 0 0-1.594 1.594l-1.051 5.558a1 1 0 0 1-1.966 0l-1.051-5.558a2 2 0 0 0-1.594-1.594l-5.558-1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0-1.966l5.558-1.051a2 2 0 0 0 1.594-1.594z\"></path><path d=\"M20 2v4\"></path><path d=\"M22 4h-4\"></path><circle cx=\"4\" cy=\"20\" r=\"2\"></circle></svg><span class=\"text-sm font-medium bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded-full\">20,000<!-- --> names</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2\">Hindi &amp; Sanskrit Names</h3><p class=\"text-sm opacity-90 leading-relaxed\">Ancient Sanskrit names connecting children to Vedic wisdom and Hindu mythology. These names draw from sacred texts and cosmic energies, each carrying vibrational frequencies believed to influence destiny.</p></div><div class=\"p-6\"><div class=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6\"><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Aarav</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Peaceful, calm</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Diya</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Light, lamp</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Karan</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Intelligent, clever</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Saanvi</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Goddess Lakshmi</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div></div><a class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700\" href=\"/names/religion/hindu/1\">Explore all <!-- -->Hindi<!-- --> names<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-right w-4 h-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m9 18 6-6-6-6\"></path></svg></a></div></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-green-500 to-green-600 p-6 text-white\"><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-moon w-8 h-8\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M20.985 12.486a9 9 0 1 1-9.473-9.472c.405-.022.617.46.402.803a6 6 0 0 0 8.268 8.268c.344-.215.825-.004.803.401\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-sm font-medium bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded-full\">8,000<!-- --> names</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2\">Hebrew Names</h3><p class=\"text-sm opacity-90 leading-relaxed\">Timeless Hebrew names from the Old Testament and Jewish tradition. These names connect to biblical stories of faith, hope, and divine purpose, carrying meanings that have inspired generations.</p></div><div class=\"p-6\"><div class=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6\"><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Elijah</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">My God is Yahweh</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Sarah</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Princess, noblewoman</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Noah</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Rest, comfort</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Rachel</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Ewe, gentle one</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div></div><a class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700\" href=\"/names/religion/christian/1\">Explore all <!-- -->Hebrew<!-- --> names<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-right w-4 h-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m9 18 6-6-6-6\"></path></svg></a></div></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-blue-600 p-6 text-white\"><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-star w-8 h-8\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M11.525 2.295a.53.53 0 0 1 .95 0l2.31 4.679a2.123 2.123 0 0 0 1.595 1.16l5.166.756a.53.53 0 0 1 .294.904l-3.736 3.638a2.123 2.123 0 0 0-.611 1.878l.882 5.14a.53.53 0 0 1-.771.56l-4.618-2.428a2.122 2.122 0 0 0-1.973 0L6.396 21.01a.53.53 0 0 1-.77-.56l.881-5.139a2.122 2.122 0 0 0-.611-1.879L2.16 9.795a.53.53 0 0 1 .294-.906l5.165-.755a2.122 2.122 0 0 0 1.597-1.16z\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-sm font-medium bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded-full\">5,000<!-- --> names</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2\">Greek Names</h3><p class=\"text-sm opacity-90 leading-relaxed\">Elegant Greek names from classical antiquity and early Christian tradition. These names embody philosophy, mythology, and the rich cultural heritage of ancient Greece and the Byzantine Empire.</p></div><div class=\"p-6\"><div class=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6\"><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Sophia</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Wisdom</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Alexander</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Defender of mankind</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Theodore</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Gift of God</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Chloe</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Blooming, green shoot</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div></div><a class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700\" href=\"/names/religion/christian/1\">Explore all <!-- -->Greek<!-- --> names<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-right w-4 h-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m9 18 6-6-6-6\"></path></svg></a></div></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-100 overflow-hidden hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-500 to-pink-600 p-6 text-white\"><div class=\"flex items-center justify-between mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-globe w-8 h-8\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><circle cx=\"12\" cy=\"12\" r=\"10\"></circle><path d=\"M12 2a14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0 20 14.5 14.5 0 0 0 0-20\"></path><path d=\"M2 12h20\"></path></svg><span class=\"text-sm font-medium bg-white/20 px-3 py-1 rounded-full\">12,000<!-- --> names</span></div><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold mb-2\">Other Languages</h3><p class=\"text-sm opacity-90 leading-relaxed\">Names from diverse cultures including Persian, Turkish, Celtic, Norse, and Native American traditions. Explore unique names that celebrate global diversity and multicultural heritage.</p></div><div class=\"p-6\"><div class=\"grid grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6\"><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Aiden</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Little fire</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-blue-100 text-blue-700\">male</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Luna</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Moon</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Kai</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Sea</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-purple-100 text-purple-700\">unisex</span></div><div class=\"p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl\"><p class=\"font-bold text-gray-900\">Zuri</p><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600\">Beautiful</p><span class=\"text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full mt-1 inline-block bg-pink-100 text-pink-700\">female</span></div></div><a class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-700\" href=\"/names/religion/christian/1\">Explore all <!-- -->Other<!-- --> names<svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-chevron-right w-4 h-4\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"m9 18 6-6-6-6\"></path></svg></a></div></div></div></div></section><section class=\"py-12 sm:py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-50 to-teal-50/30\"><div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center\">Understanding Multilingual Names</h2><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 sm:gap-8\"><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"w-12 h-12 bg-cyan-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-quote w-6 h-6 text-cyan-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path><path d=\"M5 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path></svg></div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">The Power of Original Language</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Names carry their deepest meaning in their original language. For example, the Arabic name &quot;Yusuf&quot; carries nuances of patience and divine blessing that transcend simple translation. Understanding the original pronunciation and cultural context enriches the name&#x27;s significance.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"w-12 h-12 bg-cyan-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-quote w-6 h-6 text-cyan-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path><path d=\"M5 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path></svg></div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">Cross-Cultural Adaptations</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Many names travel across cultures, adapting to new languages while retaining core meanings. &quot;Maryam&quot; becomes &quot;Mary&quot; in English and &quot;Maria&quot; in Spanish, yet all honor the same biblical figure. These variations reflect the beautiful interconnectedness of human cultures.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"w-12 h-12 bg-cyan-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-quote w-6 h-6 text-cyan-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path><path d=\"M5 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path></svg></div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">Pronunciation Matters</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Correct pronunciation honors the name&#x27;s cultural origin and preserves its intended sound and rhythm. Language-specific names often have unique phonetic qualities that contribute to their meaning. For example, Sanskrit names use specific tongue positions believed to create positive vibrations.</p></div></div></div></section><section class=\"py-12 sm:py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-white\"><div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center\">Most Popular Names by Language</h2><div class=\"overflow-x-auto\"><table class=\"w-full text-left\"><thead><tr class=\"border-b-2 border-gray-200\"><th class=\"pb-4 font-semibold text-gray-900\">Language</th><th class=\"pb-4 font-semibold text-gray-900\">Top Boy Names</th><th class=\"pb-4 font-semibold text-gray-900\">Top Girl Names</th><th class=\"pb-4 font-semibold text-gray-900\">Total Names</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr class=\"border-b border-gray-100\"><td class=\"py-4\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Arabic/Urdu</span></td><td class=\"py-4 text-gray-600\">Muhammad, Ali, Omar, Yusuf</td><td class=\"py-4 text-gray-600\">Fatima, Aisha, Maryam, Khadija</td><td class=\"py-4 font-semibold\">40,000+</td></tr><tr class=\"border-b border-gray-100\"><td class=\"py-4\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Sanskrit/Hindi</span></td><td class=\"py-4 text-gray-600\">Aarav, Vihaan, Arjun, Krish</td><td class=\"py-4 text-gray-600\">Ananya, Priya, Diya, Saanvi</td><td class=\"py-4 font-semibold\">20,000+</td></tr><tr class=\"border-b border-gray-100\"><td class=\"py-4\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Hebrew/Greek</span></td><td class=\"py-4 text-gray-600\">Noah, Elijah, David, Jacob</td><td class=\"py-4 text-gray-600\">Sophia, Emma, Olivia, Sarah</td><td class=\"py-4 font-semibold\">13,000+</td></tr><tr><td class=\"py-4\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Multicultural</span></td><td class=\"py-4 text-gray-600\">James, Alexander, Michael, Ethan</td><td class=\"py-4 text-gray-600\">Chloe, Luna, Aurora, Maya</td><td class=\"py-4 font-semibold\">12,000+</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></section><section class=\"py-12 sm:py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-50 to-teal-50/30\"><div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center\">Understanding Multilingual Names</h2><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 sm:gap-8\"><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"w-12 h-12 bg-cyan-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-quote w-6 h-6 text-cyan-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path><path d=\"M5 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path></svg></div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">The Power of Original Language</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Names carry their deepest meaning in their original language. For example, the Arabic name &quot;Yusuf&quot; carries nuances of patience and divine blessing that transcend simple translation. Understanding the original pronunciation and cultural context enriches the name&#x27;s significance.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"w-12 h-12 bg-cyan-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-quote w-6 h-6 text-cyan-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path><path d=\"M5 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path></svg></div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">Cross-Cultural Adaptations</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Many names travel across cultures, adapting to new languages while retaining core meanings. &quot;Maryam&quot; becomes &quot;Mary&quot; in English and &quot;Maria&quot; in Spanish, yet all honor the same biblical figure. These variations reflect the beautiful interconnectedness of human cultures.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-lg border border-gray-100 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300\"><div class=\"w-12 h-12 bg-cyan-100 rounded-xl flex items-center justify-center mb-4\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-quote w-6 h-6 text-cyan-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path><path d=\"M5 3a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v6a2 2 0 0 0 2 2 1 1 0 0 1 1 1v1a2 2 0 0 1-2 2 1 1 0 0 0-1 1v2a1 1 0 0 0 1 1 6 6 0 0 0 6-6V5a2 2 0 0 0-2-2z\"></path></svg></div><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">Pronunciation Matters</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Correct pronunciation honors the name&#x27;s cultural origin and preserves its intended sound and rhythm. Language-specific names often have unique phonetic qualities that contribute to their meaning. For example, Sanskrit names use specific tongue positions believed to create positive vibrations.</p></div></div></div></section><section class=\"py-12 sm:py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-white\"><div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center\">Pronunciation Guide for Multilingual Names</h2><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 sm:gap-8\"><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-50 to-purple-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-indigo-100\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-indigo-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-sparkles w-5 h-5 text-indigo-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M11.017 2.814a1 1 0 0 1 1.966 0l1.051 5.558a2 2 0 0 0 1.594 1.594l5.558 1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0 1.966l-5.558 1.051a2 2 0 0 0-1.594 1.594l-1.051 5.558a1 1 0 0 1-1.966 0l-1.051-5.558a2 2 0 0 0-1.594-1.594l-5.558-1.051a1 1 0 0 1 0-1.966l5.558-1.051a2 2 0 0 0 1.594-1.594z\"></path><path d=\"M20 2v4\"></path><path d=\"M22 4h-4\"></path><circle cx=\"4\" cy=\"20\" r=\"2\"></circle></svg>Why Pronunciation Matters</h3><p class=\"text-indigo-800 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4\">Correct pronunciation honors the name&#x27;s cultural origin and preserves its intended sound and rhythm. Language-specific names often have unique phonetic qualities that contribute to their meaning. For example, Sanskrit names use specific tongue positions believed to create positive vibrations.</p><div class=\"bg-white/50 rounded-xl p-4\"><p class=\"text-indigo-700 text-sm font-medium\">Tip: When in doubt, ask native speakers or use online pronunciation guides to ensure you honor the name&#x27;s cultural heritage.</p></div></div><div class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-50 to-teal-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border border-cyan-100\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-cyan-900 mb-4 flex items-center gap-2\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-moon w-5 h-5 text-cyan-600\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M20.985 12.486a9 9 0 1 1-9.473-9.472c.405-.022.617.46.402.803a6 6 0 0 0 8.268 8.268c.344-.215.825-.004.803.401\"></path></svg>Original vs. Localized Pronunciation</h3><p class=\"text-cyan-800 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4\">Many families choose to honor the original pronunciation as a way to preserve cultural heritage. However, localized pronunciations are also common and acceptable. The key is finding a balance that feels right for your family and community while respecting the name&#x27;s roots.</p><div class=\"bg-white/50 rounded-xl p-4\"><p class=\"text-cyan-700 text-sm font-medium\">Example: &quot;Maryam&quot; (Arabic) can be pronounced as Mary-ahm, Muh-ry-am, or Mar-yam depending on cultural context.</p></div></div></div><div class=\"mt-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-fuchsia-50/30 rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-purple-100 p-8\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-purple-900 mb-6 text-center\">Common Pronunciation Challenges</h3><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6\"><div class=\"text-center\"><div class=\"w-14 h-14 bg-purple-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3\"><span class=\"text-purple-600 font-bold text-lg\">A</span></div><p class=\"text-purple-800 text-sm font-medium\">Arabic Names</p><p class=\"text-purple-600 text-xs mt-1\">Emphasis on throat sounds and vowel length</p></div><div class=\"text-center\"><div class=\"w-14 h-14 bg-fuchsia-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3\"><span class=\"text-fuchsia-600 font-bold text-lg\">S</span></div><p class=\"text-fuchsia-800 text-sm font-medium\">Sanskrit Names</p><p class=\"text-fuchsia-600 text-xs mt-1\">Retroflex consonants and specific tongue positions</p></div><div class=\"text-center\"><div class=\"w-14 h-14 bg-cyan-100 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-3\"><span class=\"text-cyan-600 font-bold text-lg\">H</span></div><p class=\"text-cyan-800 text-sm font-medium\">Hebrew Names</p><p class=\"text-cyan-600 text-xs mt-1\">Guttural sounds like &#x27;ch&#x27; (ח) and &#x27;kh&#x27; (כ)</p></div></div></div></div></section><section class=\"py-12 sm:py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-50 to-teal-50/30\"><div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center\">Language-Specific Names FAQ</h2><div class=\"grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6\"><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-6\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">Are language-specific names harder to pronounce?</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">It depends on the language and your community. Arabic and Sanskrit names may require practice, but many parents find that people quickly learn to pronounce their child\\&#x27;s name correctly. Consider providing a phonetic spelling when introducing the name.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-6\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">Should I use the original language pronunciation?</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Many families choose to honor the original pronunciation as a way to preserve cultural heritage. However, localized pronunciations are also common and acceptable. Consider what feels right for your family and community.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-6\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">Can non-native speakers use these names?</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Absolutely! Many parents choose names from languages other than their own. The key is to understand and respect the name\\&#x27;s meaning and cultural significance, and to learn proper pronunciation to honor its origin.</p></div><div class=\"bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg border border-gray-200 p-6\"><h3 class=\"text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3\">Which language has the most baby names?</h3><p class=\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\">Arabic/Urdu has the largest collection with over 40,000 names, followed by Sanskrit/Hindi with 20,000+ names. This reflects the rich naming traditions and linguistic diversity of these cultures.</p></div></div><script type=\"application/ld+json\">{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Are language-specific names harder to pronounce?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"It depends on the language and your community. Arabic and Sanskrit names may require practice, but many parents find that people quickly learn to pronounce their child's name correctly.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can non-native speakers use these names?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Absolutely! Many parents choose names from languages other than their own. The key is to understand and respect the name's meaning and cultural significance.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Which language has the most baby names?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Arabic/Urdu has the largest collection with over 40,000 names, followed by Sanskrit/Hindi with 20,000+ names.\"}}]}</script></div></section><section class=\"py-12 sm:py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-600 to-teal-600\"><div class=\"max-w-7xl mx-auto text-center\"><h2 class=\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-6\">Discover Names from Around the World</h2><p class=\"text-lg text-cyan-100 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto\">Explore 60,000+ verified baby names from Urdu, Arabic, Hindi, Sanskrit, Hebrew, Greek, and many more languages. Find the perfect multicultural name that honors your heritage or embraces global diversity.</p><div class=\"flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center\"><a class=\"px-8 py-4 bg-white text-cyan-600 rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-cyan-50 transition-all shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl\" href=\"/languages\">Explore by Language</a><a class=\"px-8 py-4 bg-cyan-500 text-white rounded-xl font-bold text-lg hover:bg-cyan-400 transition-all border-2 border-white/20 shadow-lg h