 has the most baby names?\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed\",\"children\":\"Arabic/Urdu has the largest collection with over 40,000 names, followed by Sanskrit/Hindi with 20,000+ names. This reflects the rich naming traditions and linguistic diversity of these cultures.\"}]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"FAQPage\\\",\\\"mainEntity\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Are language-specific names harder to pronounce?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"It depends on the language and your community. Arabic and Sanskrit names may require practice, but many parents find that people quickly learn to pronounce their child's name correctly.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Can non-native speakers use these names?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Absolutely! Many parents choose names from languages other than their own. The key is to understand and respect the name's meaning and cultural significance.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Which language has the most baby names?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Arabic/Urdu has the largest collection with over 40,000 names, followed by Sanskrit/Hindi with 20,000+ names.\\\"}}]}\"}}]]}]}]\n11:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"py-12 sm:py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-600 to-teal-600\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"max-w-7xl mx-auto text-center\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-6\",\"children\":\"Discover Names from Around the World\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-lg text-cyan-100 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto\",\"children\":\"Explore 60,000+ verified b